[[File:Johann Adam Benckiser.jpg|thumb|Johann Adam Benckiser]] '''Johann Adam Benckiser''' (30 December 1782 – 7 May 1851) was the founder of [[JAB Holding Company|Joh. A. Benckiser GmbH]], a major German chemicals business. The business has been part of [[Reckitt Benckiser]], a constituent of the [[FTSE 100 Index]], since 1999.
==Career== Benckiser founded a business in [[Pforzheim]], Germany specialising in industrial and consumer goods industrial chemicals in 1823.<ref name=slash>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2012/may/09/reckitt-benckiser-shareholders-slash-stake|title=Reckitt Benckiser's largest shareholder to slash stake|date=9 May 2012|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=9 April 2017}}</ref> He initially made [[ammonia]], [[hydrochloric acid]] and [[ammonium chloride]].<ref>{{cite book|title=FMCG: The Power of Fast-Moving Consumer Goods|first= Greg|last= Thain |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=i8MABAAAQBAJ&pg=PA379&lpg=PA379&dq=Johann+Adam+Benckiser&source=bl&ots=YfxX9BTmkQ&sig=VJ2sOqpwT16qMunn-TKQ5OC7sdo&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiJu7Wbt5jTAhWSF8AKHWiaDC8Q6AEIdzAS#v=onepage&q=Johann%20Adam%20Benckiser&f=false|page=379|publisher=First Edition Design|year=2014|isbn=978-1622-876-48-8}}</ref> Karl Ludwig Reimann, a chemist, joined the business in 1828 and married Benckiser's daughter.<ref name=ft>{{cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/242db7ea-d1a8-11e5-831d-09f7778e7377|title=Germany’s intensely private and immensely wealthy Reimann family|publisher=FT.com|date=11 March 2016|accessdate=9 April 2017}}</ref> Benckiser died in May 1851.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=W_XFDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA604&lpg=PA604&dq=%22Johann+Adam+Benckiser%22&source=bl&ots=U4L3RE5ta6&sig=rl9tOYikDYOwI5j5aN5NYUI0BTo&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi1vvfFvpjTAhWpD8AKHQqdC0I4FBDoAQgZMAA#v=onepage&q=%22Johann%20Adam%20Benckiser%22&f=false|title=Leopold Gmelin (1788 - 1853): Leben und Werk eines Heidelberger Chemikers|first=Petra |last=Stumm|page=604|publisher=Centaurus Verlag & Media|year=2012|isbn=978-3-86226-179-6}}</ref> Since then the company has been owned and enlarged by the Reimann family. In the 1980s it became a substantial company under the guidance of manager Peter Harf.<ref name=ft/>
