'''Uzi Katz''' (born September 1960) is an Israeli businessman and the chief executive officer of [[Telit]] until it was uncovered that '''Oozi Cats''' was allegedly the same person as '''Uzi Katz''', who was indicted for property fraud in the United States in the 1990s.<ref name="Guardian">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/aug/14/telit-communications-chief-oozi-cats-us|title=Telit Communications chief fired after fraud allegations|first1=Shane|last1=Hickey|first2=Rupert|last2=Neate|date=14 August 2017|publisher=|accessdate=14 August 2017|via=The Guardian}}</ref><ref name="bbc.co.uk">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-40921599|title=Telit chief Oozi Cats resigns after US fraud allegations|author=|date=14 August 2017|publisher=|accessdate=14 August 2017|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>
Katz was the founder and head of Auto Depot Israel.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=http://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/business/1.806068|title=Oozi Cats or Uzi Katz? Tech CEO Takes Leave of Absence After Past Indictment Surfaces|first=Omri|last=Zerachovitz|date=10 August 2017|publisher=|accessdate=14 August 2017|via=Haaretz}}</ref>
In 1992, Katz, an associate, and his wife Ruth were indicted by a Boston [[district court]] over allegations of [[wire fraud]], but the couple left the US before the plea hearing.<ref name="timesofisrael.com">{{cite web|url=http://jewishnews.timesofisrael.com/italian-paper-claims-s-fugitive-uzi-katz-and-tech-boss-oozi-cats-is-the-same-person/|title=Italian paper claims U.S. fugitive Uzi Katz and tech boss Oozi Cats is the same person|author=|date=|website=timesofisrael.com|accessdate=14 August 2017}}</ref>
Cats co-founded [[Telit]] and was its CEO since 2000.<ref name="bbc.co.uk"/>
In August 2017, Share Prophets, a financial blog, and the Italian newspaper ''[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]'' had both noticed that Cats and Katz both had wives called Ruth, and had the same birthday.<ref name="Guardian" />
In August 2017, Cats took "a voluntary leave of absence" from Telit, and resigned a few days later, following allegations that he had misled them about this real identity for 17 years, and was a fugitive from US justice.<ref name="Guardian"/><ref name="timesofisrael.com"/><ref name="globes">{{cite web|url=http://www.globes.co.il/en/article-telit-announces-ceo-oozi-cats-stepping-down-1001201158|title=Globes English - Telit announces CEO Oozi Cats stepping down|website=globes.co.il|accessdate=15 August 2017}}</ref> Following the announcement, shares in Telit, which is listed on London's [[Alternative Investment Market|AIM]] stock exchange, fell by 35%.<ref name="auto"/>
